The Chronicle 10:14 – A 15-member Independence Flame Torch relay team is waiting to get things rolling. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-601027" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-10.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-10.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-10-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-601024" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-11.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-11.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-11-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The team will light a torch and move to the city centre, Makokoba, Mzilikazi suburbs and Barbourfields Stadium, where the main celebrations are taking place. There President Mnangagwa will light the Independence Flame. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-601032" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-8.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-8.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-8-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> 10:10 – Scenes at Mkoba Stadium in Gweru where the provincial independence celebrations are taking place <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-601021" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-6.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-6.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-6-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> It has been drizzling since 6AM and people are braving the chilly weather to celebrate the Uhuru. 10:03 – People are making their way to Barbourfields Stadium where the main Independence Day celebrations are being held. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-601014" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Already there are long winding queues outside the stadium. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-601008" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Indeoendence-5.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Indeoendence-5.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Indeoendence-5-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> People who will come late, risk being turned away. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-601015" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> PREAMBLE HISTORY is being made in Bulawayo today as the city, for the first time since 1980, hosts the country’s main Independence celebrations at Barbourfields Stadium in line with the Second Republic’s devolution and decentralisation thrust. The Independence Day celebrations  are being held under the theme: “Zim@ 42 — Leaving no one and no place behind.” In the past, Independence Day celebrations were held in Harare. Thousands of Zimbabweans are expected to gather at the iconic football field for the momentous event that will be spiced up by entertainment from schoolchildren, musicians, Zimbabwe Defence Forces, Zimbabwe Republic Police, Zimbabwe Prisons and Correctional Service drills, among others. <img class="size-full wp-image-600988" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Childrens-party.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Childrens-party.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Childrens-party-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa hosted the Children’s Party at State House in Bulawayo ahead of today’s main celebrations The Children’s Party held at State House in yesterday ran under the same theme. President Mnangagwa hosted the Children’s Party at State House in Bulawayo ahead of today’s main celebrations. Also yesterday, the Independence Flame and Independence Trophy were taken on a seven-hour tour of Bulawayo’s western suburbs. <img class="size-full wp-image-600985" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-of-the-flame-.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-of-the-flame-.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-of-the-flame--360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Independence Flame touring Bulawayo suburbs From Saturday, The Independence Flame was resting at Khami National Monument and was  guarded by members of the police overnight. In the morning a convoy of security details took the flame from the top of the King’s enclosure at the Khami National Monument, mounted it on the back of a truck, then it was taken to koBullet in Nketa. <img class="size-full wp-image-600984" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Uhuru-Flame-at-Joshua-Nkomos-statue.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Uhuru-Flame-at-Joshua-Nkomos-statue.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Uhuru-Flame-at-Joshua-Nkomos-statue-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Uhuru Flame at the Joshua Nkomo statue There, Government officials such as Minister Ncube welcomed it, with Zimbabwe football giants, Highlanders and Dynamos supporters, officials and players and residents waiting for the Independence Flame. The two teams then joined the convoy, as a way to hype their match today at Barbourfields Stadium as they play for the Independence Trophy. Highlanders FC captain Ariel Sibanda and his Dynamos counterpart Partson Jaure were at the back of a pick-up parading the Independence Trophy. <img class="size-full wp-image-600982" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Bosso-captains-.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Bosso-captains-.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Bosso-captains--360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Highlanders FC captain Ariel Sibanda and his Dynamos counterpart Partson Jaure At midnight there was a fireworks display at the Tower Block Municipal. <img class="size-full wp-image-600979" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/fireworks-.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/fireworks-.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/fireworks--360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Fireworks lit up the Bulawayo night sky at midnight Join us for live updates from Barbourfields Stadium.